flavor: Bulbasaur can be seen napping in bright sunlight. There is a seed on its back. By soaking up the sun’s rays, the seed grows progressively larger.
name: Bulbasaur

flavor: There is a bud on this Pokémon’s back. To support its weight, Ivysaur’s legs and trunk grow thick and strong. If it starts spending more time lying in the sunlight, it’s a sign that the bud will bloom into a large flower soon.
name: Ivysaur

flavor: There is a large flower on Venusaur’s back. The flower is said to take on vivid colors if it gets plenty of nutrition and sunlight. The flower’s aroma soothes the emotions of people.
name: Venusaur

flavor: The flame that burns at the tip of its tail is an indication of its emotions. The flame wavers when Charmander is enjoying itself. If the Pokémon becomes enraged, the flame burns fiercely.
name: Charmander

flavor: Charmeleon mercilessly destroys its foes using its sharp claws. If it encounters a strong foe, it turns aggressive. In this excited state, the flame at the tip of its tail flares with a bluish white color.
name: Charmeleon

flavor: Charizard flies around the sky in search of powerful opponents. It breathes fire of such great heat that it melts anything. However, it never turns its fiery breath on any opponent weaker than itself.
name: Charizard

flavor: Squirtle’s shell is not merely used for protection. The shell’s rounded shape and the grooves on its surface help minimize resistance in water, enabling this Pokémon to swim at high speeds.
name: Squirtle

flavor: Its tail is large and covered with a rich, thick fur. The tail becomes increasingly deeper in color as Wartortle ages. The scratches on its shell are evidence of this Pokémon’s toughness as a battler.
name: Wartortle

flavor: Blastoise has water spouts that protrude from its shell. The water spouts are very accurate. They can shoot bullets of water with enough accuracy to strike empty cans from a distance of over 160 feet.
name: Blastoise

flavor: Caterpie has a voracious appetite. It can devour leaves bigger than its body right before your eyes. From its antenna, this Pokémon releases a terrifically strong odor.
name: Caterpie

flavor: The shell covering this Pokémon’s body is as hard as an iron slab. Metapod does not move very much. It stays still because it is preparing its soft innards for evolution inside the hard shell.
name: Metapod

flavor: Butterfree has a superior ability to search for delicious honey from flowers. It can even search out, extract, and carry honey from flowers that are blooming over six miles from its nest.
name: Butterfree

flavor: Weedle ha un senso dell’olfatto estremamente sviluppato. Riesce a distinguere le sue foglie preferite da quelle che lo disgustano semplicemente annusandole con il grande naso rosso.
name: Weedle

flavor: Kakuna remains virtually immobile as it clings to a tree. However, on the inside, it is extremely busy as it prepares for its coming evolution. This is evident from how hot the shell becomes to the touch.
name: Kakuna

flavor: Beedrill is extremely territorial. No one should ever approach its nest—this is for their own safety. If angered, they will attack in a furious swarm.
name: Beedrill

flavor: Pidgey has an extremely sharp sense of direction. It is capable of unerringly returning home to its nest, however far it may be removed from its familiar surroundings.
name: Pidgey

flavor: Pidgeotto claims a large area as its own territory. This Pokémon flies around, patrolling its living space. If its territory is violated, it shows no mercy in thoroughly punishing the foe with its sharp claws.
name: Pidgeotto

flavor: This Pokémon has a dazzling plumage of beautifully glossy feathers. Many Trainers are captivated by the striking beauty of the feathers on its head, compelling them to choose Pidgeot as their Pokémon.
name: Pidgeot

flavor: Rattata is cautious in the extreme. Even while it is asleep, it constantly listens by moving its ears around. It is not picky about where it lives—it will make its nest anywhere.
name: Rattata

flavor: Raticate’s sturdy fangs grow steadily. To keep them ground down, it gnaws on rocks and logs. It may even chew on the walls of houses.
name: Raticate

flavor: Spearow emette un grido molto acuto, percepibile anche a 1 km di distanza. Quando questo grido riecheggia nei dintorni, questo Pokémon intende avvertire i suoi simili di un pericolo imminente.
name: Spearow

flavor: Fearow is recognized by its long neck and elongated beak. They are conveniently shaped for catching prey in soil or water. It deftly moves its long and skinny beak to pluck prey.
name: Fearow

flavor: Ekans curls itself up in a spiral while it rests. Assuming this position allows it to quickly respond to a threat from any direction with a glare from its upraised head.
name: Ekans

flavor: This Pokémon is terrifically strong in order to constrict things with its body. It can even flatten steel oil drums. Once Arbok wraps its body around its foe, escaping its crunching embrace is impossible.
name: Arbok

flavor: Quando Pikachu incontra qualcosa che non conosce, lo colpisce con una scarica elettrica. Quando si vede una bacca annerita, è evidente che questo Pokémon ha emesso una scossa troppo forte.
name: Pikachu

flavor: If the electrical sacs become excessively charged, Raichu plants its tail in the ground and discharges. Scorched patches of ground will be found near this Pokémon’s nest.
name: Raichu

flavor: Sandshrew’s body is configured to absorb water without waste, enabling it to survive in an arid desert. This Pokémon curls up to protect itself from its enemies.
name: Sandshrew

flavor: Sandslash’s body is covered by tough spikes, which are hardened sections of its hide. Once a year, the old spikes fall out, to be replaced with new spikes that grow out from beneath the old ones.
name: Sandslash

flavor: Nidoran♀ has barbs that secrete a powerful poison. They are thought to have developed as protection for this small-bodied Pokémon. When enraged, it releases a horrible toxin from its horn.
name: Nidoran-f

flavor: When Nidorina are with their friends or family, they keep their barbs tucked away to prevent hurting each other. This Pokémon appears to become nervous if separated from the others.
name: Nidorina

flavor: Nidoqueen’s body is encased in extremely hard scales. It is adept at sending foes flying with harsh tackles. This Pokémon is at its strongest when it is defending its young.
name: Nidoqueen

flavor: Nidoran♂ has developed muscles for moving its ears. Thanks to them, the ears can be freely moved in any direction. Even the slightest sound does not escape this Pokémon’s notice.
name: Nidoran-m

flavor: Nidorino has a horn that is harder than a diamond. If it senses a hostile presence, all the barbs on its back bristle up at once, and it challenges the foe with all its might.
name: Nidorino

flavor: Nidoking’s thick tail packs enormously destructive power. With one swing, it can topple a metal transmission tower. Once this Pokémon goes on a rampage, there is no stopping it.
name: Nidoking

flavor: In ogni notte di luna piena questi Pokémon escono in gruppo a giocare. All’alba i Clefairy tornano stanchi nella quiete delle loro tane montane e vanno a dormire stretti fra loro.
name: Clefairy

flavor: Algunos científicos sostienen que cuando mira al cielo fijamente en las noches de luna llena es porque siente morriña.
name: Clefable

flavor: At the time of its birth, Vulpix has one white tail. The tail separates into six if this Pokémon receives plenty of love from its Trainer. The six tails become magnificently curled.
name: Vulpix

flavor: Ninetales casts a sinister light from its bright red eyes to gain total control over its foe’s mind. This Pokémon is said to live for a thousand years.
name: Ninetales

flavor: Jigglypuff’s vocal cords can freely adjust the wavelength of its voice. This Pokémon uses this ability to sing at precisely the right wavelength to make its foes most drowsy.
name: Jigglypuff

flavor: Wigglytuff è dotato di occhi grandi come dischi, resi lucidi da un sottile strato lacrimale in superficie. Se gli va della polvere negli occhi, questa è lavata via subito.
name: Wigglytuff

flavor: Zubat remains quietly unmoving in a dark spot during the bright daylight hours. It does so because prolonged exposure to the sun causes its body to become slightly burned.
name: Zubat

flavor: Golbat loves to drink the blood of living things. It is particularly active in the pitch black of night. This Pokémon flits around in the night skies, seeking fresh blood.
name: Golbat

flavor: During the daytime, Oddish buries itself in soil to absorb nutrients from the ground using its entire body. The more fertile the soil, the glossier its leaves become.
name: Oddish

flavor: Gloom releases a foul fragrance from the pistil of its flower. When faced with danger, the stench worsens. If this Pokémon is feeling calm and secure, it does not release its usual stinky aroma.
name: Gloom

flavor: Vileplume’s toxic pollen triggers atrocious allergy attacks. That’s why it is advisable never to approach any attractive flowers in a jungle, however pretty they may be.
name: Vileplume

flavor: Paras has parasitic mushrooms growing on its back called tochukaso. They grow large by drawing nutrients from this Bug Pokémon host. They are highly valued as a medicine for extending life.
name: Paras

flavor: Parasect is known to infest large trees en masse and drain nutrients from the lower trunk and roots. When an infested tree dies, they move onto another tree all at once.
name: Parasect

flavor: Venonat is said to have evolved with a coat of thin, stiff hair that covers its entire body for protection. It possesses large eyes that never fail to spot even minuscule prey.
name: Venonat

flavor: Venomoth is nocturnal—it is a Pokémon that only becomes active at night. Its favorite prey are small insects that gather around streetlights, attracted by the light in the darkness.
name: Venomoth

flavor: Diglett are raised in most farms. The reason is simple— wherever this Pokémon burrows, the soil is left perfectly tilled for planting crops. This soil is made ideal for growing delicious vegetables.
name: Diglett

flavor: Dugtrio are actually triplets that emerged from one body. As a result, each triplet thinks exactly like the other two triplets. They work cooperatively to burrow endlessly.
name: Dugtrio

flavor: Meowth withdraws its sharp claws into its paws to slinkily sneak about without making any incriminating footsteps. For some reason, this Pokémon loves shiny coins that glitter with light.
name: Meowth

flavor: Persian has six bold whiskers that give it a look of toughness. The whiskers sense air movements to determine what is in the Pokémon’s surrounding vicinity. It becomes docile if grabbed by the whiskers.
name: Persian

flavor: Psyduck uses a mysterious power. When it does so, this Pokémon generates brain waves that are supposedly only seen in sleepers. This discovery spurred controversy among scholars.
name: Psyduck

flavor: The webbed flippers on its forelegs and hind legs and the streamlined body of Golduck give it frightening speed. This Pokémon is definitely much faster than even the most athletic swimmer.
name: Golduck

flavor: When Mankey starts shaking and its nasal breathing turns rough, it’s a sure sign that it is becoming angry. However, because it goes into a towering rage almost instantly, it is impossible for anyone to flee its wrath.
name: Mankey

flavor: When Primeape becomes furious, its blood circulation is boosted. In turn, its muscles are made even stronger. However, it also becomes much less intelligent at the same time.
name: Primeape

flavor: Growlithe has a superb sense of smell. Once it smells anything, this Pokémon won’t forget the scent, no matter what. It uses its advanced olfactory sense to determine the emotions of other living things.
name: Growlithe

flavor: Arcanine is known for its high speed. It is said to be capable of running over 6,200 miles in a single day and night. The fire that blazes wildly within this Pokémon’s body is its source of power.
name: Arcanine

flavor: Poliwag has a very thin skin. It is possible to see the Pokémon’s spiral innards right through the skin. Despite its thinness, however, the skin is also very flexible. Even sharp fangs bounce right off it.
name: Poliwag

flavor: The surface of Poliwhirl’s body is always wet and slick with a slimy fluid. Because of this slippery covering, it can easily slip and slide out of the clutches of any enemy in battle.
name: Poliwhirl

flavor: Poliwrath’s highly developed, brawny muscles never grow fatigued, however much it exercises. It is so tirelessly strong, this Pokémon can swim back and forth across the ocean without effort.
name: Poliwrath

flavor: Abra duerme 18 horas al día, pero puede detectar a cualquier enemigo que se le acerque mientras duerme. En una situación así, usa Teletransporte para protegerse.
name: Abra

flavor: Kadabra emits a peculiar alpha wave if it develops a headache. Only those people with a particularly strong psyche can hope to become a Trainer of this Pokémon.
name: Kadabra

flavor: Alakazam’s brain continually grows, making its head far too heavy to support with its neck. This Pokémon holds its head up using its psychokinetic power instead.
name: Alakazam

flavor: Machop’s muscles are special—they never get sore no matter how much they are used in exercise. This Pokémon has sufficient power to hurl a hundred adult humans.
name: Machop

flavor: Machoke’s thoroughly toned muscles possess the hardness of steel. This Pokémon has so much strength, it can easily hold aloft a sumo wrestler on just one finger.
name: Machoke

flavor: Machamp has the power to hurl anything aside. However, trying to do any work requiring care and dexterity causes its arms to get tangled. This Pokémon tends to leap into action before it thinks.
name: Machamp

flavor: Bellsprout’s thin and flexible body lets it bend and sway to avoid any attack, however strong it may be. From its mouth, this Pokémon spits a corrosive fluid that melts even iron.
name: Bellsprout

flavor: Weepinbell has a large hook on its rear end. At night, the Pokémon hooks on to a tree branch and goes to sleep. If it moves around in its sleep, it may wake up to find itself on the ground.
name: Weepinbell

flavor: Victreebel has a long vine that extends from its head. This vine is waved and flicked about as if it were an animal to attract prey. When an unsuspecting prey draws near, this Pokémon swallows it whole.
name: Victreebel

flavor: Tentacool’s body is largely composed of water. If it is removed from the sea, it dries up like parchment. If this Pokémon happens to become dehydrated, put it back into the sea.
name: Tentacool

flavor: Tentacruel has large red orbs on its head. The orbs glow before lashing the vicinity with a harsh ultrasonic blast. This Pokémon’s outburst creates rough waves around it.
name: Tentacruel

flavor: The longer a Geodude lives, the more its edges are chipped and worn away, making it more rounded in appearance. However, this Pokémon’s heart will remain hard, craggy, and rough always.
name: Geodude

flavor: Graveler grows by feeding on rocks. Apparently, it prefers to eat rocks that are covered in moss. This Pokémon eats its way through a ton of rocks on a daily basis.
name: Graveler

flavor: Golem live up on mountains. If there is a large earthquake, these Pokémon will come rolling down off the mountains en masse to the foothills below.
name: Golem

flavor: Ponyta is very weak at birth. It can barely stand up. This Pokémon becomes stronger by stumbling and falling to keep up with its parent.
name: Ponyta

flavor: Rapidash usually can be seen casually cantering in the fields and plains. However, when this Pokémon turns serious, its fiery manes flare and blaze as it gallops its way up to 150 mph.
name: Rapidash

flavor: Slowpoke uses its tail to catch prey by dipping it in water at the side of a river. However, this Pokémon often forgets what it’s doing and often spends entire days just loafing at water’s edge.
name: Slowpoke

flavor: Slowbro’s tail has a Shellder firmly attached with a bite. As a result, the tail can’t be used for fishing anymore. This causes Slowbro to grudgingly swim and catch prey instead.
name: Slowbro

flavor: Magnemite attaches itself to power lines to feed on electricity. If your house has a power outage, check your circuit breakers. You may find a large number of this Pokémon clinging to the breaker box.
name: Magnemite

flavor: Magneton emits a powerful magnetic force that is fatal to mechanical devices. As a result, large cities sound sirens to warn citizens of large-scale outbreaks of this Pokémon.
name: Magneton

flavor: Farfetch’d is always seen with a stalk from a plant of some sort. Apparently, there are good stalks and bad stalks. This Pokémon has been known to fight with others over stalks.
name: Farfetchd

flavor: Doduo’s two heads never sleep at the same time. Its two heads take turns sleeping, so one head can always keep watch for enemies while the other one sleeps.
name: Doduo

flavor: Watch out if Dodrio’s three heads are looking in three separate directions. It’s a sure sign that it is on its guard. Don’t go near this Pokémon if it’s being wary—it may decide to peck you.
name: Dodrio

flavor: Seel hunts for prey in the frigid sea underneath sheets of ice. When it needs to breathe, it punches a hole through the ice with the sharply protruding section of its head.
name: Seel

flavor: Dewgong loves to snooze on bitterly cold ice. The sight of this Pokémon sleeping on a glacier was mistakenly thought to be a mermaid by a mariner long ago.
name: Dewgong

flavor: Grimer’s sludgy and rubbery body can be forced through any opening, however small it may be. This Pokémon enters sewer pipes to drink filthy wastewater.
name: Grimer

flavor: From Muk’s body seeps a foul fluid that gives off a nose-bendingly horrible stench. Just one drop of this Pokémon’s body fluid can turn a pool stagnant and rancid.
name: Muk

flavor: Di notte Shellder usa la sua lingua larga per scavare una buca sul fondo del mare e infilarcisi per dormire. Quando dorme chiude la conchiglia ma lascia la lingua fuori a penzoloni.
name: Shellder

flavor: Cloyster is capable of swimming in the sea. It does so by swallowing water, then jetting it out toward the rear. This Pokémon shoots spikes from its shell using the same system.
name: Cloyster

flavor: Gastly is largely composed of gaseous matter. When exposed to a strong wind, the gaseous body quickly dwindles away. Groups of this Pokémon cluster under the eaves of houses to escape the ravages of wind.
name: Gastly

flavor: Haunter is a dangerous Pokémon. If one beckons you while floating in darkness, you must never approach it. This Pokémon will try to lick you with its tongue and steal your life away.
name: Haunter

flavor: Talvolta, nelle notti buie, può accadere che un passante sia improvvisamente assalito dalla propria ombra. È opera di Gengar, che usa avvicinarsi fingendosi un’ombra.
name: Gengar

flavor: Onix has a magnet in its brain. It acts as a compass so that this Pokémon does not lose direction while it is tunneling. As it grows older, its body becomes increasingly rounder and smoother.
name: Onix

flavor: If your nose becomes itchy while you are sleeping, it’s a sure sign that one of these Pokémon is standing above your pillow and trying to eat your dream through your nostrils.
name: Drowzee

flavor: Hypno holds a pendulum in its hand. The arcing movement and glitter of the pendulum lull the foe into a deep state of hypnosis. While this Pokémon searches for prey, it polishes the pendulum.
name: Hypno

flavor: Krabby live on beaches, burrowed inside holes dug into the sand. On sandy beaches with little in the way of food, these Pokémon can be seen squabbling with each other over territory.
name: Krabby

flavor: Kingler has an enormous, oversized claw. It waves this huge claw in the air to communicate with others. However, because the claw is so heavy, the Pokémon quickly tires.
name: Kingler

flavor: Voltorb was first sighted at a company that manufactures Poké Balls. The link between that sighting and the fact that this Pokémon looks very similar to a Poké Ball remains a mystery.
name: Voltorb

flavor: Electrode eats electricity in the atmosphere. On days when lightning strikes, you can see this Pokémon exploding all over the place from eating too much electricity.
name: Electrode

flavor: This Pokémon consists of six eggs that form a closely knit cluster. The six eggs attract each other and spin around. When cracks increasingly appear on the eggs, Exeggcute is close to evolution.
name: Exeggcute

flavor: Exeggutor originally came from the tropics. Its heads steadily grow larger from exposure to strong sunlight. It is said that when the heads fall off, they group together to form Exeggcute.
name: Exeggutor

flavor: Cubone pines for the mother it will never see again. Seeing a likeness of its mother in the full moon, it cries. The stains on the skull the Pokémon wears are made by the tears it sheds.
name: Cubone

flavor: Marowak si evolve da Cubone dopo aver superato il lutto per la perdita della madre ed essersi fatto forte. Questo Pokémon dall’animo forgiato e temprato non si fa prendere facilmente dallo sconforto.
name: Marowak

flavor: Hitmonlee’s legs freely contract and stretch. Using these springlike legs, it bowls over foes with devastating kicks. After battle, it rubs down its legs and loosens the muscles to overcome fatigue.
name: Hitmonlee

flavor: Hitmonchan is said to possess the spirit of a boxer who had been working toward a world championship. This Pokémon has an indomitable spirit and will never give up in the face of adversity.
name: Hitmonchan

flavor: Whenever Lickitung comes across something new, it will unfailingly give it a lick. It does so because it memorizes things by texture and by taste. It is somewhat put off by sour things.
name: Lickitung

flavor: If Koffing becomes agitated, it raises the toxicity of its internal gases and jets them out from all over its body. This Pokémon may also overinflate its round body, then explode.
name: Koffing

flavor: Weezing loves the gases given off by rotted kitchen garbage. This Pokémon will find a dirty, unkempt house and make it its home. At night, when the people in the house are asleep, it will go through the trash.
name: Weezing

flavor: Rhyhorn runs in a straight line, smashing everything in its path. It is not bothered even if it rushes headlong into a block of steel. This Pokémon may feel some pain from the collision the next day, however.
name: Rhyhorn

flavor: Rhydon’s horn can crush even uncut diamonds. One sweeping blow of its tail can topple a building. This Pokémon’s hide is extremely tough. Even direct cannon hits don’t leave a scratch.
name: Rhydon

flavor: Chansey lays nutritionally excellent eggs on an everyday basis. The eggs are so delicious, they are easily and eagerly devoured by even those people who have lost their appetite.
name: Chansey

flavor: Tangela’s vines snap off easily if they are grabbed. This happens without pain, allowing it to make a quick getaway. The lost vines are replaced by newly grown vines the very next day.
name: Tangela

flavor: If you come across a young Kangaskhan playing by itself, you must never disturb it or attempt to catch it. The baby Pokémon’s parent is sure to be in the area, and it will become violently enraged at you.
name: Kangaskhan

flavor: Horsea eats small insects and moss off of rocks. If the ocean current turns fast, this Pokémon anchors itself by wrapping its tail around rocks or coral to prevent being washed away.
name: Horsea

flavor: Seadra sleeps after wriggling itself between the branches of coral. Those trying to harvest coral are occasionally stung by this Pokémon’s poison barbs if they fail to notice it.
name: Seadra

flavor: Goldeen is a very beautiful Pokémon with fins that billow elegantly in water. However, don’t let your guard down around this Pokémon—it could ram you powerfully with its horn.
name: Goldeen

flavor: In the autumn, Seaking males can be seen performing courtship dances in riverbeds to woo females. During this season, this Pokémon’s body coloration is at its most beautiful.
name: Seaking

flavor: Staryu’s center section has an organ called the core that shines bright red. If you go to a beach toward the end of summer, the glowing cores of these Pokémon look like the stars in the sky.
name: Staryu

flavor: Starmie’s center section—the core—glows brightly in seven colors. Because of its luminous nature, this Pokémon has been given the nickname “the gem of the sea.”
name: Starmie

flavor: Mr. Mime is a master of pantomime. Its gestures and motions convince watchers that something unseeable actually exists. Once the watchers are convinced, the unseeable thing exists as if it were real.
name: Mr-mime

flavor: Scyther is blindingly fast. Its blazing speed enhances the effectiveness of the twin scythes on its forearms. This Pokémon’s scythes are so effective, they can slice through thick logs in one wicked stroke.
name: Scyther

flavor: Jynx walks rhythmically, swaying and shaking its hips as if it were dancing. Its motions are so bouncingly alluring, people seeing it are compelled to shake their hips without giving any thought to what they are doing.
name: Jynx

flavor: When a storm arrives, gangs of this Pokémon compete with each other to scale heights that are likely to be stricken by lightning bolts. Some towns use Electabuzz in place of lightning rods.
name: Electabuzz

flavor: In lotta, Magmar sputa fiamme roventi da tutto il corpo per intimidire l’avversario. La sua furia irruente provoca ondate di calore che bruciano tutta la vegetazione attorno a lui.
name: Magmar

flavor: Pinsir is astoundingly strong. It can grip a foe weighing twice its weight in its horns and easily lift it. This Pokémon’s movements turn sluggish in cold places.
name: Pinsir

flavor: This Pokémon is not satisfied unless it is rampaging at all times. If there is no opponent for Tauros to battle, it will charge at thick trees and knock them down to calm itself.
name: Tauros

flavor: Magikarp is a pathetic excuse for a Pokémon that is only capable of flopping and splashing. This behavior prompted scientists to undertake research into it.
name: Magikarp

flavor: When Magikarp evolves into Gyarados, its brain cells undergo a structural transformation. It is said that this transformation is to blame for this Pokémon’s wildly violent nature.
name: Gyarados

flavor: People have driven Lapras almost to the point of extinction. In the evenings, this Pokémon is said to sing plaintively as it seeks what few others of its kind still remain.
name: Lapras

flavor: Ditto rearranges its cell structure to transform itself into other shapes. However, if it tries to transform itself into something by relying on its memory, this Pokémon manages to get details wrong.
name: Ditto

flavor: Eevee has an unstable genetic makeup that suddenly mutates due to the environment in which it lives. Radiation from various stones causes this Pokémon to evolve.
name: Eevee

flavor: Vaporeon underwent a spontaneous mutation and grew fins and gills that allow it to live underwater. This Pokémon has the ability to freely control water.
name: Vaporeon

flavor: Jolteon’s cells generate a low level of electricity. This power is amplified by the static electricity of its fur, enabling the Pokémon to drop thunderbolts. The bristling fur is made of electrically charged needles.
name: Jolteon

flavor: La morbida pelliccia di Flareon ha uno scopo ben preciso: libera calore nell’aria in modo da abbassare la temperatura corporea, che nel caso di questo Pokémon può raggiungere anche 900 °C.
name: Flareon

flavor: Porygon is capable of reverting itself entirely back to program data and entering cyberspace. This Pokémon is copy protected so it cannot be duplicated by copying.
name: Porygon

flavor: Omanyte is one of the ancient and long-since-extinct Pokémon that have been regenerated from fossils by people. If attacked by an enemy, it withdraws itself inside its hard shell.
name: Omanyte

flavor: Omastar uses its tentacles to capture its prey. It is believed to have become extinct because its shell grew too large and heavy, causing its movements to become too slow and ponderous.
name: Omastar

flavor: Kabuto is a Pokémon that has been regenerated from a fossil. However, in extremely rare cases, living examples have been discovered. The Pokémon has not changed at all for 300 million years.
name: Kabuto

flavor: Kabutops swam underwater to hunt for its prey in ancient times. The Pokémon was apparently evolving from being a water dweller to living on land as evident from the beginnings of change in its gills and legs.
name: Kabutops

flavor: Aerodactyl risale all’epoca dei dinosauri. È stato rigenerato da materiale genetico estratto dall’ambra. Si suppone che in tempi antichi fosse considerato il signore dei cieli.
name: Aerodactyl

flavor: Snorlax’s typical day consists of nothing more than eating and sleeping. It is such a docile Pokémon that there are children who use its expansive belly as a place to play.
name: Snorlax

flavor: Articuno is a legendary bird Pokémon that can control ice. The flapping of its wings chills the air. As a result, it is said that when this Pokémon flies, snow will fall.
name: Articuno

flavor: Zapdos is a legendary bird Pokémon that has the ability to control electricity. It usually lives in thunderclouds. The Pokémon gains power if it is stricken by lightning bolts.
name: Zapdos

flavor: Moltres is a legendary bird Pokémon that has the ability to control fire. If this Pokémon is injured, it is said to dip its body in the molten magma of a volcano to burn and heal itself.
name: Moltres

flavor: Dratini continually molts and sloughs off its old skin. It does so because the life energy within its body steadily builds to reach uncontrollable levels.
name: Dratini

flavor: Dragonair stores an enormous amount of energy inside its body. It is said to alter weather conditions in its vicinity by discharging energy from the crystals on its neck and tail.
name: Dragonair

flavor: Dragonite is capable of circling the globe in just 16 hours. It is a kindhearted Pokémon that leads lost and foundering ships in a storm to the safety of land.
name: Dragonite

flavor: Mewtwo is a Pokémon that was created by genetic manipulation. However, even though the scientific power of humans created this Pokémon’s body, they failed to endow Mewtwo with a compassionate heart.
name: Mewtwo

flavor: Mew is said to possess the genetic composition of all Pokémon. It is capable of making itself invisible at will, so it entirely avoids notice even if it approaches people.
name: Mew

flavor: A sweet aroma gently wafts from the leaf on its head. It is docile and loves to soak up the sun's rays.
name: Chikorita

flavor: The buds that ring its neck give off a spicy aroma that perks people up.
name: Bayleef

flavor: The aroma that rises from its petals contains a substance that calms aggressive feelings.
name: Meganium

flavor: It is timid, and always curls it­ self up in a ball. If attacked, it flares up its back for protection.
name: Cyndaquil

flavor: Be careful if it turns its back during battle. It means that it will attack with the fire on its back.
name: Quilava

flavor: If its rage peaks, it becomes so hot that anything that touches it will instantly go up in flames.
name: Typhlosion

flavor: Its well-developed jaws are powerful and capable of crushing anything. Even its trainer must be careful.
name: Totodile

flavor: If it loses a fang, a new one grows back in its place. There are always 48 fangs lining its mouth.
name: Croconaw

flavor: When it bites with its massive and powerful jaws, it shakes its head and savagely tears its victim up.
name: Feraligatr

flavor: A very cautious POKéMON, it raises itself up using its tail to get a better view of its surroundings.
name: Sentret

flavor: The mother puts its offspring to sleep by curling up around them. It corners foes with speed.
name: Furret

flavor: It always stands on one foot. It changes feet so fast, the movement can rarely be seen.
name: Hoothoot

flavor: Its eyes are specially adapted. They concentrate even faint light and enable it to see in the dark.
name: Noctowl

flavor: It is very timid. It will be afraid to move if it is alone. But it will be active if it is in a group.
name: Ledyba

flavor: When the stars flicker in the night sky, it flutters about, scattering a glowing powder.
name: Ledian

flavor: It lies still in the same pose for days in its web, waiting for its unsuspecting prey to wander close.
name: Spinarak

flavor: It spins string not only from its rear but also from its mouth. It is hard to tell which end is which.
name: Ariados

flavor: It flies so si­ lently through the dark on its four wings that it may not be noticed even when nearby.
name: Crobat

flavor: It shoots positive and negative elec­ tricity between the tips of its two antennae and zaps its enemies.
name: Chinchou

flavor: The light it emits is so bright that it can illuminate the sea's surface from a depth of over three miles.
name: Lanturn

flavor: It is not yet skilled at storing electricity. It may send out a jolt if amused or startled.
name: Pichu

flavor: According to local rumors, Cleffa are often seen in places where shooting stars have fallen.
name: Cleffa

flavor: It has a very soft body. If it starts to roll, it will bounce all over and be impossible to stop.
name: Igglybuff

flavor: The shell seems to be filled with joy. It is said that it will share good luck when treated kindly.
name: Togepi

flavor: They say that it will appear before kindhearted, car­ ing people and shower them with happiness.
name: Togetic

flavor: Because its wings aren't yet fully grown, it has to hop to get around. It is always star­ ing at something.
name: Natu

flavor: They say that it stays still and quiet because it is seeing both the past and future at the same time.
name: Xatu

flavor: If static elec­ tricity builds in its body, its fleece doubles in volume. Touching it will shock you.
name: Mareep

flavor: As a result of storing too much electricity, it developed patches where even downy wool won't grow.
name: Flaaffy

flavor: The tail's tip shines brightly and can be seen from far away. It acts as a beacon for lost people.
name: Ampharos

flavor: BELLOSSOM gather at times and appear to dance. They say that the dance is a ritual to summon the sun.
name: Bellossom

flavor: The tip of its tail, which con­ tains oil that is lighter than wa­ ter, lets it swim without drowning.
name: Marill

flavor: By keeping still and listening in­ tently, it can tell what is in even wild, fast- moving rivers.
name: Azumarill

flavor: Although it always pretends to be a tree, its composi­ tion appears to be closer to a rock than a plant.
name: Sudowoodo

flavor: If POLIWAG and POLIWHIRL hear its echoing cry, they respond by gather­ ing from far and wide.
name: Politoed

flavor: To keep from being blown away by the wind, they gather in clusters. They do enjoy gentle breezes, though.
name: Hoppip

flavor: The bloom on top of its head opens and closes as the temperature fluc­ tuates up and down.
name: Skiploom

flavor: Once it catches the wind, it deft­ ly controls its cotton-puff spores to float, even around the world.
name: Jumpluff

flavor: Its tail is so powerful that it can use it to grab a tree branch and hold itself up in the air.
name: Aipom

flavor: It may drop out of the sky suddenly. If attacked by a SPEAROW, it will violently shake its leaves.
name: Sunkern

flavor: It converts sun­ light into energy. In the darkness after sunset, it closes its petals and becomes still.
name: Sunflora

flavor: If it flaps its wings really fast, it can generate shock waves that will shatter win­ dows in the area.
name: Yanma

flavor: This POKéMON lives in cold water. It will leave the water to search for food when it gets cold outside.
name: Wooper

flavor: This carefree POKéMON has an easy-going nature. While swimming, it always bumps into boat hulls.
name: Quagsire

flavor: It uses the fine hair that covers its body to sense air currents and predict its ene­ my's actions.
name: Espeon

flavor: When agitated, this POKéMON pro­ tects itself by spraying poisonous sweat from its pores.
name: Umbreon

flavor: Feared and loathed by many, it is believed to bring misfortune to all those who see it at night.
name: Murkrow

flavor: It has incredible intellect and in­ tuition. Whatever the situation, it remains calm and collected.
name: Slowking

flavor: It likes playing mischievous tricks such as screaming and wailing to startle people at night.
name: Misdreavus

flavor: Its flat, thin body is always stuck on walls. Its shape appears to have some meaning.
name: Unown

flavor: It hates light and shock. If attack­ ed, it inflates its body to pump up its counter­ strike.
name: Wobbuffet

flavor: Its tail has a small brain of its own. Beware! If you get close, it may react to your scent and bite.
name: Girafarig

flavor: It likes to make its shell thicker by adding layers of tree bark. The additional weight doesn't bother it.
name: Pineco

flavor: Its entire body is shielded by a steel-hard shell. What lurks inside the armor is a total mystery.
name: Forretress

flavor: DUNSPARCE has a drill for its tail. It uses this tail to burrow into the ground backwards. This POKéMON is known to make its nest in complex shapes deep under the ground.
name: Dunsparce

flavor: It flies straight at its target’s face, then clamps down on the startled victim to inject poison.
name: Gligar

flavor: Its body has been compressed deep under the ground. As a result, it is even harder than a diamond.
name: Steelix

flavor: Although it looks frightening, it is actually kind and affectionate. It is very popular among women.
name: Snubbull

flavor: It is actually timid and easily spooked. If at­ tacked, it flails about to fend off its attacker.
name: Granbull

flavor: To fire its poison spikes, it must inflate its body by drinking over 2.6 gallons of water all at once.
name: Qwilfish

flavor: It swings its eye- patterned pincers up to scare its foes. This makes it look like it has three heads.
name: Scizor

flavor: The BERRIES it stores in its vase-like shell decompose and become a gooey liquid.
name: Shuckle

flavor: This powerful POKéMON thrusts its prized horn under its enemies’ bellies then lifts and throws them.
name: Heracross

flavor: Its paws conceal sharp claws. If attacked, it sud­ denly extends the claws and startles its enemy.
name: Sneasel

flavor: If it finds honey, its crescent mark glows. It always licks its paws because they are soaked with honey.
name: Teddiursa

flavor: Although it is a good climber, it prefers to snap trees with its forelegs and eat fallen BERRIES.
name: Ursaring

flavor: Its body is made of magma. If it doesn’t keep moving, its body will cool and harden.
name: Slugma

flavor: The shell on its back is just skin that has cooled and hardened. It breaks easily with a slight touch.
name: Magcargo

flavor: It rubs its snout on the ground to find and dig up food. It sometimes discovers hot springs.
name: Swinub

flavor: Because the long hair all over its body obscures its sight, it just keeps charging repeatedly.
name: Piloswine

flavor: It continuously sheds and grows. The tip of its head is prized as a treasure for its beauty.
name: Corsola

flavor: It squirts water forcefully from its mouth to shoot down flying prey.
name: Remoraid

flavor: It traps enemies with its suction- cupped tentacles then smashes them with its rock-hard head.
name: Octillery

flavor: It carries food all day long. There are tales about lost people who were saved by the food it had.
name: Delibird

flavor: As it majestically swims, it doesn't care if REMORAID attach to it for scavenging its leftovers.
name: Mantine

flavor: Its sturdy wings look heavy, but they are actually hollow and light, allowing it to fly freely in the sky.
name: Skarmory

flavor: It uses different kinds of cries for communicating with others of its kind and for pursuing its prey.
name: Houndour

flavor: If you are burned by the flames it shoots from its mouth, the pain will never go away.
name: Houndoom

flavor: It is said that it usually hides in underwater caves. It can create whirlpools by yawning.
name: Kingdra

flavor: It swings its long snout around play­ fully, but because it is so strong, that can be dan­ gerous.
name: Phanpy

flavor: It has sharp, hard tusks and a rugged hide. Its TACKLE is strong enough to knock down a house.
name: Donphan

flavor: This upgraded version of PORYGON is designed for space exploration. It can't fly, though.
name: Porygon2

flavor: Those who stare at its antlers will gradually lose control of their senses and be unable to stand.
name: Stantler

flavor: A special fluid oozes from the tip of its tail. It paints the fluid everywhere to mark its territory.
name: Smeargle

flavor: It is always bursting with en­ ergy. To make it­ self stronger, it keeps on fighting even if it loses.
name: Tyrogue

flavor: If you become enchanted by its smooth, elegant, dance-like kicks, you may get drilled hard.
name: Hitmontop

flavor: Its lips are the most sensitive parts on its body. It always uses its lips first to examine things.
name: Smoochum

flavor: It generates electricity by whirling its arms. However, it can’t store the energy it makes.
name: Elekid

flavor: Each and every time it inhales and exhales, hot embers dribble out of its mouth and nostrils.
name: Magby

flavor: Its milk is packed with nutrition, making it the ultimate beverage for the sick or weary.
name: Miltank

flavor: Anyone who takes even one bite of BLISSEY's egg be­ comes unfailingly caring and pleas­ ant to everyone.
name: Blissey

flavor: The rain clouds it carries let it fire thunderbolts at will. They say that it descended with lightning.
name: Raikou

flavor: Volcanoes erupt when it barks. Un­ able to restrain its extreme power, it races headlong around the land.
name: Entei

flavor: Said to be the reincarnation of north winds, it can instantly purify filthy, murky water.
name: Suicune

flavor: It feeds on soil. After it has eaten a large mountain, it will fall asleep so it can grow.
name: Larvitar

flavor: Its shell is as hard as sheet rock, and it is also very strong. Its THRASHING can topple a mountain.
name: Pupitar

flavor: Its body can't be harmed by any sort of attack, so it is very eager to make challenges against enemies.
name: Tyranitar

flavor: It is said that it quietly spends its time deep at the bottom of the sea because its powers are too strong.
name: Lugia

flavor: Legends claim this POKéMON flies the world's skies con­ tinuously on its magnificent seven- colored wings.
name: Ho-oh

flavor: This POKéMON wan­ ders across time. Grass and trees flourish in the forests in which it has appeared.
name: Celebi

flavor: TREECKO has small hooks on the bottom of its feet that enable it to scale vertical walls. This POKéMON attacks by slamming foes with its thick tail.
name: Treecko

flavor: The leaves growing out of GROVYLE’s body are convenient for camouflaging it from enemies in the forest. This POKéMON is a master at climbing trees in jungles.
name: Grovyle

flavor: The leaves growing on SCEPTILE’s body are very sharp edged. This POKéMON is very agile - it leaps all over the branches of trees and jumps on its foe from above or behind.
name: Sceptile

flavor: TORCHIC sticks with its TRAINER, following behind with unsteady steps. This POKéMON breathes fire of over 1,800 degrees F, including fireballs that leave the foe scorched black.
name: Torchic

flavor: COMBUSKEN toughens up its legs and thighs by running through fields and mountains. This POKéMON’s legs possess both speed and power, enabling it to dole out ten kicks in one second.
name: Combusken

flavor: In battle, BLAZIKEN blows out intense flames from its wrists and attacks foes courageously. The stronger the foe, the more intensely this POKéMON’s wrists burn.
name: Blaziken

flavor: The fin on MUDKIP’s head acts as highly sensitive radar. Using this fin to sense movements of water and air, this POKéMON can determine what is taking place around it without using its eyes.
name: Mudkip

flavor: The surface of MARSHTOMP’s body is enveloped by a thin, sticky film that enables it to live on land. This POKéMON plays in mud on beaches when the ocean tide is low.
name: Marshtomp

flavor: SWAMPERT is very strong. It has enough power to easily drag a boulder weighing more than a ton. This POKéMON also has powerful vision that lets it see even in murky water.
name: Swampert

flavor: At first sight, POOCHYENA takes a bite at anything that moves. This POKéMON chases after prey until the victim becomes exhausted. However, it may turn tail if the prey strikes back.
name: Poochyena

flavor: MIGHTYENA gives obvious signals when it is preparing to attack. It starts to growl deeply and then flattens its body. This POKéMON will bite savagely with its sharply pointed fangs.
name: Mightyena

flavor: ZIGZAGOON restlessly wanders everywhere at all times. This POKéMON does so because it is very curious. It becomes interested in anything that it happens to see.
name: Zigzagoon

flavor: LINOONE always runs full speed and only in straight lines. If facing an obstacle, it makes a right-angle turn to evade it. This POKéMON is very challenged by gently curving roads.
name: Linoone

flavor: Using the spikes on its rear end,   WURMPLE peels the bark off trees and feeds on the sap that oozes out. This POKéMON’s feet are tipped with suction pads that allow it to cling to glass without slipping.
name: Wurmple

flavor: SILCOON tethers itself to a tree branch using silk to keep from falling. There,  this POKéMON hangs quietly while it awaits evolution. It peers out of the silk cocoon through a small hole.
name: Silcoon

flavor: BEAUTIFLY’s favorite food is the sweet pollen of flowers. If you want to see this POKéMON, just leave a potted flower by an open window. BEAUTIFLY is sure to come looking for pollen.
name: Beautifly

flavor: CASCOON makes its protective cocoon by wrapping its body entirely with a fine silk from its mouth. Once the silk goes around its body, it hardens. This POKéMON prepares for its evolution inside the cocoon.
name: Cascoon

flavor: DUSTOX is instinctively drawn to light. Swarms of this POKéMON are attracted by the bright lights of cities, where they wreak havoc by stripping the leaves off roadside trees for food.
name: Dustox

flavor: LOTAD live in ponds and lakes, where they float on the surface. It grows weak if its broad leaf dies. On rare occasions, this POKéMON travels on land in search of clean water.
name: Lotad

flavor: LOMBRE is nocturnal - it will get active after dusk. It is also a mischief-maker. When this POKéMON spots anglers, it tugs on their fishing lines from beneath the surface and enjoys their consternation.
name: Lombre

flavor: LUDICOLO begins dancing as soon as it hears cheerful, festive music. This POKéMON is said to appear when it hears the singing of children on hiking outings.
name: Ludicolo

flavor: SEEDOT attaches itself to a tree branch using the top of its head. It sucks moisture from the tree while hanging off the branch. The more water it drinks, the glossier this POKéMON’s body becomes.
name: Seedot

flavor: NUZLEAF live in densely overgrown forests. They occasionally venture out of the forest to startle people. This POKéMON dislikes having its long nose pinched.
name: Nuzleaf

flavor: SHIFTRY is a mysterious POKéMON that is said to live atop towering trees  dating back over a thousand years. It creates terrific windstorms with the fans it holds.
name: Shiftry

flavor: TAILLOW courageously stands its ground against foes, however strong they may be. This gutsy POKéMON will remain defiant even after a loss. On the other hand, it cries loudly if it becomes hungry.
name: Taillow

flavor: SWELLOW flies high above our heads, making graceful arcs in the sky. This POKéMON dives at a steep angle as soon as it spots its prey. The hapless prey is tightly grasped by SWELLOW’s clawed feet, preventing escape.
name: Swellow

flavor: WINGULL has the habit of carrying prey and valuables in its beak and hiding them in all sorts of locations. This POKéMON rides the winds and flies as if it were skating across the sky.
name: Wingull

flavor: PELIPPER is a flying transporter that carries small POKéMON and eggs inside its massive bill. This POKéMON builds its nest on steep cliffs facing the sea.
name: Pelipper

flavor: RALTS senses the emotions of people using the horns on its head. This POKéMON rarely appears before people. But when it does, it draws closer if it senses that the person has a positive disposition.
name: Ralts

flavor: It is said that a KIRLIA that is exposed to the positive emotions of its TRAINER grows beautiful. This POKéMON controls psychokinetic powers with its highly developed brain.
name: Kirlia

flavor: GARDEVOIR has the ability to read the future. If it senses impending danger to its TRAINER, this POKéMON is said to unleash its psychokinetic energy at full power.
name: Gardevoir

flavor: From the tips of its feet, SURSKIT secretes an oil that enables it to walk on water as if it were skating. This POKéMON feeds on microscopic organisms in ponds and lakes.
name: Surskit

flavor: MASQUERAIN intimidates enemies with the eyelike patterns on its antennas. This POKéMON flaps its four wings to freely fly in any direction - even sideways and backwards - as if it were a helicopter.
name: Masquerain

flavor: SHROOMISH live in damp soil in the dark depths of forests. They are often found keeping still under fallen leaves. This POKéMON feeds on compost that is made up of fallen, rotted leaves.
name: Shroomish

flavor: BRELOOM closes in on its foe with light and sprightly footwork, then throws punches with its stretchy arms. This POKéMON’s fighting technique puts boxers to shame.
name: Breloom

flavor: SLAKOTH lolls around for over twenty hours every day. Because it moves so little, it does not need much food. This POKéMON’s sole daily meal consists of just three leaves.
name: Slakoth

flavor: VIGOROTH is always itching and agitated to go on a wild rampage. It simply can’t tolerate sitting still for even a minute. This POKéMON’s stress level rises if it can’t be moving constantly.
name: Vigoroth

flavor: SLAKING spends all day lying down and lolling about. It eats grass growing within its reach. If it eats all the grass it can reach, this POKéMON reluctantly moves to another spot.
name: Slaking

flavor: NINCADA lives underground for many years in complete darkness. This POKéMON absorbs nutrients from the roots of trees. It stays motionless as it waits for evolution.
name: Nincada

flavor: NINJASK moves around at such a high speed that it cannot be seen, even while its crying can be clearly heard. For that reason, this POKéMON was long believed to be invisible.
name: Ninjask

flavor: A discarded bug shell that came to life. Peering into the crack on its back is said to steal one’s spirit.
name: Shedinja

flavor: Normally, WHISMUR’s voice is very quiet - it is barely audible even if one is paying close attention. However, if this POKéMON senses danger, it starts crying at an earsplitting volume.
name: Whismur

flavor: LOUDRED’s bellowing can completely decimate a wood-frame house. It uses its voice to punish its foes. This POKéMON’s round ears serve as loudspeakers.
name: Loudred

flavor: EXPLOUD triggers earthquakes with the tremors it creates by bellowing. If this POKéMON violently inhales from the ports on its body, it’s a sign that it is preparing to let loose a huge bellow.
name: Exploud

flavor: MAKUHITA is tenacious - it will keep getting up and attacking its foe however many times it is knocked down. Every time it gets back up, this POKéMON stores more energy in its body for evolving.
name: Makuhita

flavor: HARIYAMA practices its straight-arm slaps in any number of locations. One hit of this POKéMON’s powerful, openhanded, straight-arm punches could snap a telephone pole in two.
name: Hariyama

flavor: AZURILL spins its tail as if it were a lasso, then hurls it far. The momentum of the throw sends its body flying, too. Using this unique action, one of these POKéMON managed to hurl itself a record 33 feet.
name: Azurill

flavor: NOSEPASS’s magnetic nose is always pointed to the north. If two of these POKéMON meet, they cannot turn their faces to each other when they are close because their magnetic noses repel one another.
name: Nosepass

flavor: SKITTY has the habit of becoming fascinated by moving objects and chasing them around. This POKéMON is known to chase after its own tail and become dizzy.
name: Skitty

flavor: DELCATTY prefers to live an unfettered existence in which it can do as it pleases at its own pace. Because this POKéMON eats and sleeps whenever it decides, its daily routines are completely random.
name: Delcatty

flavor: SABLEYE lead quiet lives deep inside caverns. They are feared, however, because these POKéMON are thought to steal the spirits of people when their eyes burn with a sinister glow in the darkness.
name: Sableye

flavor: MAWHILE’s huge jaws are actually steel horns that have been transformed. Its docile-looking face serves to lull its foe into letting down its guard. When the foe least expects it, MAWHILE chomps it with its gaping jaws.
name: Mawile

flavor: This POKéMON has a body of steel. To make its body, ARON feeds on iron ore that it digs from mountains. Occasionally, it causes major trouble by eating bridges and rails.
name: Aron

flavor: LAIRON tempers its steel body by drinking highly nutritious mineral springwater until it is bloated. This POKéMON makes its nest close to springs of delicious water.
name: Lairon

flavor: AGGRON claims an entire mountain as its own territory. It mercilessly beats up anything that violates its environment. This POKéMON vigilantly patrols its territory at all times.
name: Aggron

flavor: MEDITITE undertakes rigorous mental training deep in the mountains. However, whenever it meditates, this POKéMON always loses its concentration and focus. As a result, its training never ends.
name: Meditite

flavor: It is said that through meditation, MEDICHAM heightens energy inside its body and sharpens its sixth sense. This POKéMON hides its presence by merging itself with fields and mountains.
name: Medicham

flavor: ELECTRIKE stores electricity in its long body hair. This POKéMON stimulates its leg muscles with electric charges. These jolts of power give its legs explosive acceleration performance.
name: Electrike

flavor: It rarely appears before people. It is said to nest where lightning has fallen.
name: Manectric

flavor: PLUSLE always acts as a cheerleader for its partners. Whenever a teammate puts out a good effort in battle, this POKéMON shorts out its body to create the crackling noises of sparks to show its joy.
name: Plusle

flavor: MINUN is more concerned about cheering on its partners than its own safety. It shorts out the electricity in its body to create brilliant showers of sparks to cheer on its teammates.
name: Minun

flavor: With the arrival of night, VOLBEAT emits light from its tail. It communicates with others by adjusting the intensity and flashing of its light. This POKéMON is attracted by the sweet aroma of ILLUMISE.
name: Volbeat

flavor: ILLUMISE attracts a swarm of VOLBEAT using a sweet fragrance. Once the VOLBEAT have gathered, this POKéMON leads the lit-up swarm in drawing geometric designs on the canvas of the night sky.
name: Illumise

flavor: ROSELIA shoots sharp thorns as projectiles at any opponent that tries to steal the flowers on its arms. The aroma of this POKéMON brings serenity to living things.
name: Roselia

flavor: Virtually all of GULPIN’s body is its stomach. As a result, it can swallow something its own size. This POKéMON’s stomach contains a special fluid that digests anything.
name: Gulpin

flavor: It swallows anything whole. It sweats toxic fluids from its follicles to douse foes.
name: Swalot

flavor: CARVANHA’s strongly developed jaws and its sharply pointed fangs pack the destructive power to rip out boat hulls. Many boats have been attacked and sunk by this POKéMON.
name: Carvanha

flavor: Nicknamed “the bully of the sea,” SHARPEDO is widely feared. Its cruel fangs grow back immediately if they snap off. Just one of these POKéMON can thoroughly tear apart a supertanker.
name: Sharpedo

flavor: It bounces playfully like a ball. The more seawater it swallows, the higher it bounces.
name: Wailmer

flavor: WAILORD is the largest of all identified POKéMON up to now. This giant POKéMON swims languorously in the vast open sea, eating massive amounts of food at once with its enormous mouth.
name: Wailord

flavor: NUMEL is extremely dull witted - it doesn’t notice being hit. However, it can’t stand hunger for even a second. This POKéMON’s body is a seething cauldron of boiling magma.
name: Numel

flavor: CAMERUPT has a volcano inside its body. Magma of 18,000 degrees F courses through its body. Occasionally, the humps on this POKéMON’s back erupt, spewing the superheated magma.
name: Camerupt

flavor: TORKOAL digs through mountains in search of coal. If it finds some, it fills hollow spaces on its shell with the coal and burns it. If it is attacked, this POKéMON spouts thick black smoke to beat a retreat.
name: Torkoal

flavor: GRUMPIG uses the black pearls on its body to amplify its psychic power waves for gaining total control over its foe. When this POKéMON uses its special power, its snorting breath grows labored.
name: Grumpig

flavor: All the SPINDA that exist in the world are said to have utterly unique spot patterns. The shaky, tottering steps of this POKéMON give it the appearance of dancing.
name: Spinda

flavor: Its big jaws crunch through boulders. Because its head is so big, it has a hard time getting back upright if it tips over onto its back.
name: Trapinch

flavor: To make prey faint, VIBRAVA generates ultrasonic waves by vigorously making its two wings vibrate. This POKéMON’s ultrasonic waves are so powerful, they can bring on headaches in people.
name: Vibrava

flavor: FLYGON is nicknamed “the elemental  spirit of the desert.” Because its flapping wings whip up a cloud of sand, this POKéMON is always enveloped in a sandstorm while flying.
name: Flygon

flavor: CACNEA lives in arid locations such as deserts. It releases a strong aroma from its flower to attract prey. When prey comes near, this POKéMON shoots sharp thorns from its body to bring the victim down.
name: Cacnea

flavor: During the daytime, CACTURNE remains unmoving so that it does not lose any moisture to the harsh desert sun. This POKéMON becomes active at night when the temperature drops.
name: Cacturne

flavor: SWABLU has light and fluffy wings that are like cottony clouds. This POKéMON is not frightened of people. It lands on the heads of people and sits there like a cotton-fluff hat.
name: Swablu

flavor: ALTARIA dances and wheels through the sky among billowing, cotton-like clouds. By singing melodies in its crystal-clear voice, this POKéMON makes its listeners experience dreamy wonderment.
name: Altaria

flavor: Memories of battling its arch-rival SEVIPER are etched into every cell of ZANGOOSE’s body. This POKéMON adroitly dodges attacks with incredible agility.
name: Zangoose

flavor: SEVIPER shares a generations-long feud with ZANGOOSE. The scars on its body are evidence of vicious battles. This POKéMON attacks using its sword- edged tail.
name: Seviper

flavor: LUNATONE was discovered at a location where a meteorite fell. As a result, some people theorize that this POKéMON came from space. However, no one has been able to prove this theory so far.
name: Lunatone

flavor: SOLROCK is a new species of POKéMON that is said to have fallen from space. It floats in air and moves silently. In battle, this POKéMON releases intensely bright light.
name: Solrock

flavor: BARBOACH’s sensitive whiskers serve as a superb radar system. This POKéMON hides in mud, leaving only its two whiskers exposed while it waits for prey to come along.
name: Barboach

flavor: WHISCASH is extremely territorial. Just one of these POKéMON will claim a large pond as its exclusive territory. If a foe approaches it, it thrashes about and triggers a massive earthquake.
name: Whiscash

flavor: CORPHISH were originally foreign POKéMON that were imported as pets. They eventually turned up in the wild. This POKéMON is very hardy and has greatly increased its population.
name: Corphish

flavor: CRAWDAUNT has an extremely violent nature that compels it to challenge other living things to battle. Other life-forms refuse to live in ponds inhabited by this POKéMON, making them desolate places.
name: Crawdaunt

flavor: BALTOY moves while spinning around on its one foot. Primitive wall paintings depicting this POKéMON living among people were discovered in some ancient ruins.
name: Baltoy

flavor: CLAYDOL are said to be dolls of mud made by primitive humans and brought to life by exposure to a mysterious ray. This POKéMON moves about while levitating.
name: Claydol

flavor: LILEEP became extinct approximately a hundred million years ago. This ancient POKéMON attaches itself to a rock on the seafloor and catches approaching prey using tentacles  shaped like flower petals.
name: Lileep

flavor: CRADILY roams around the ocean floor in search of food. This POKéMON freely extends its tree trunk-like neck and captures unwary prey using its eight tentacles.
name: Cradily

flavor: ANORITH was regenerated from a prehistoric fossil. This primitive POKéMON once lived in warm seas. It grips its prey firmly between its two large claws.
name: Anorith

flavor: ARMALDO’s tough armor makes all attacks bounce off. This POKéMON’s two enormous claws can be freely extended or contracted. They have the power to punch right through a steel slab.
name: Armaldo

flavor: FEEBAS’s fins are ragged and tattered from the start of its life. Because of its shoddy appearance, this POKéMON is largely ignored. It is capable of living in both the sea and in rivers.
name: Feebas

flavor: MILOTIC is said to be the most beautiful of all the POKéMON. It has the power to becalm such emotions as anger and hostility to quell bitter feuding.
name: Milotic

flavor: CASTFORM’s appearance changes with the weather. This POKéMON gained the ability to use the vast power of nature to protect its tiny body.
name: Castform

flavor: KECLEON is capable of changing its body colors at will to blend in with its surroundings. There is one exception - this POKéMON can’t change the zigzag pattern on its belly.
name: Kecleon

flavor: SHUPPET is attracted by feelings of jealousy and vindictiveness. If someone develops strong feelings of vengeance, this POKéMON will appear in a swarm and line up beneath the eaves of that person’s home.
name: Shuppet

flavor: BANETTE generates energy for laying strong curses by sticking pins into its own body. This POKéMON was originally a pitiful plush doll that was thrown away.
name: Banette

flavor: DUSKULL can pass through any wall no matter how thick it may be. Once this POKéMON chooses a target, it will doggedly pursue the intended victim until the break of dawn.
name: Duskull

flavor: DUSCLOPS’s body is completely hollow - there is nothing at all inside. It is said that its body is like a black hole. This POKéMON will absorb anything into its body, but nothing will ever come back out.
name: Dusclops

flavor: The bunches of fruit around TROPIUS’s neck are very popular with children. This POKéMON loves fruit, and eats it continuously. Apparently, its love for fruit resulted in its own outgrowth of fruit.
name: Tropius

flavor: Emitting ultrasonic cries, it floats on winds to travel great distances.
name: Chimecho

flavor: Every time ABSOL appears before people, it is followed by a disaster such as an earthquake or a tidal wave. As a result, it came to be known as the disaster POKéMON.
name: Absol

flavor: WYNAUT can always be seen with a big, happy smile on its face. Look at its tail to determine if it is angry. When angered, this POKéMON will be slapping the ground with its tail.
name: Wynaut

flavor: SNORUNT live in regions with heavy snowfall. In seasons without snow, such as spring and summer, this POKéMON steals away to live quietly among stalactites and stalagmites deep in caverns.
name: Snorunt

flavor: GLALIE has a body made of rock, which it hardens with an armor of ice. This POKéMON has the ability to freeze moisture in the atmosphere into any shape it desires.
name: Glalie

flavor: SPHEAL is much faster rolling than  walking to get around. When groups of this POKéMON eat, they all clap at once to show their pleasure. Because of this, their mealtimes are noisy.
name: Spheal

flavor: SEALEO has the habit of always juggling on the tip of its nose anything it sees for the first time. This POKéMON occasionally entertains itself by balancing and rolling a SPHEAL on its nose.
name: Sealeo

flavor: WALREIN’s two massively developed tusks can totally shatter blocks of ice weighing ten tons with one blow. This POKéMON’s thick coat of blubber insulates it from subzero temperatures.
name: Walrein

flavor: CLAMPERL’s sturdy shell is not only good for protection - it is also used for clamping and catching prey. A fully grown CLAMPERL’s shell will be scored with nicks and scratches all over.
name: Clamperl

flavor: It lives deep in the pitch-dark sea. It attracts prey by moving its tail in mimicry of a small animal.
name: Huntail

flavor: GOREBYSS lives in the southern seas at extreme depths. Its body is built to withstand the enormous pressure of water at incredible depths. Because of this, this POKéMON’s body is unharmed by ordinary attacks.
name: Gorebyss

flavor: It has remained unchanged for 100 million years. It was discovered during a deep-sea exploration.
name: Relicanth

flavor: LUVDISC live in shallow seas in the tropics. This heart-shaped POKéMON earned its name by swimming after loving couples it spotted in the ocean’s waves.
name: Luvdisc

flavor: BAGON has a dream of one day soaring in the sky. In doomed efforts to fly, this POKéMON hurls itself off cliffs. As a result of its dives, its head has  grown tough and as hard as tempered steel.
name: Bagon

flavor: Inside SHELGON’s armor-like shell, cells are in the midst of transformation to create an entirely new body. This POKéMON’s shell is extremely heavy, making its movements sluggish.
name: Shelgon

flavor: SALAMENCE came about as a result of a strong, long-held dream of growing wings. It is said that this powerful desire triggered a sudden mutation in this POKéMON’s cells, causing it to sprout its magnificent wings.
name: Salamence

flavor: Its cells are all magnetic, and it communicates with others by using magnetic pulses.
name: Beldum

flavor: When two BELDUM fuse together, METANG is formed. The brains of the BELDUM are joined by a magnetic nervous system. By linking its brains magnetically, this POKéMON generates strong psychokinetic power.
name: Metang

flavor: METAGROSS has four brains in total. Combined, the four brains can breeze through difficult calculations faster than a supercomputer. This POKéMON can float in the air by tucking in its four legs.
name: Metagross

flavor: REGIROCK was sealed away by people long ago. If this POKéMON’s body is damaged in battle, it is said to seek out suitable rocks on its own to repair itself.
name: Regirock

flavor: REGICE’s body was made during an ice age. The deep-frozen body can’t be melted, even by fire. This POKéMON controls frigid air of minus 328 degrees F.
name: Regice

flavor: REGISTEEL has a body that is harder than any kind of metal. Its body is apparently hollow. No one has any idea what this POKéMON eats.
name: Registeel

flavor: LATIAS is highly sensitive to the emotions of people. If it senses any hostility, this POKéMON ruffles the feathers all over its body and cries shrilly to intimidate the foe.
name: Latias

flavor: LATIOS has the ability to make its foe see an image of what it has seen or imagines in its head. This POKéMON is intelligent and understands human speech.
name: Latios

flavor: KYOGRE has the power to create massive rain clouds that cover the entire sky and bring about torrential downpours. This POKéMON saved people who were suffering from droughts.
name: Kyogre

flavor: GROUDON has long been described in  mythology as the POKéMON that raised lands and expanded continents. This POKéMON took to sleep after a cataclysmic battle with KYOGRE.
name: Groudon

flavor: RAYQUAZA lived for hundreds of millions of years in the earth’s ozone layer,  never descending to the ground. This POKéMON appears to feed on water and particles in the atmosphere.
name: Rayquaza

flavor: A legend states that JIRACHI will make true any wish that is written on notes attached to its head when it awakens. If this POKéMON senses danger, it will fight without awakening.
name: Jirachi

flavor: The DNA of a space virus underwent a sudden mutation upon exposure to a laser beam and resulted in DEOXYS. The crystalline organ on this POKéMON’s chest appears to be its brain.
name: Deoxys

flavor: Made from soil, the shell on its back hardens when it drinks water. It lives along lakes.
name: Turtwig

flavor: It lives along water in forests. In the daytime, it leaves the forest to sunbathe its treed shell.
name: Grotle

flavor: Small Pokémon occasionally gather on its unmoving back to begin building their nests.
name: Torterra

flavor: It agilely scales sheer cliffs to live atop craggy mountains. Its fire is put out when it sleeps.
name: Chimchar

flavor: To intimidate attackers, it stretches the fire on its tail to make itself appear bigger.
name: Monferno

flavor: It uses a special kind of martial arts involving all its limbs. Its fire never goes out.
name: Infernape

flavor: Because it is very proud, it hates accepting food from people. Its thick down guards it from cold.
name: Piplup

flavor: It lives alone, away from others. Apparently, every one of them believes it is the most important.
name: Prinplup

flavor: The three horns that extend from its beak attest to its power. The leader has the biggest horns.
name: Empoleon

flavor: They flock in great numbers. Though small, they flap their wings with great power.
name: Starly

flavor: It flies around forests and fields in search of bug Pokémon. It stays within a huge flock.
name: Staravia

flavor: It has a savage nature. It will courageously challenge foes that are much larger.
name: Staraptor

flavor: With nerves of steel, nothing can perturb it. It is more agile and active than it appears.
name: Bidoof

flavor: It makes its nest by damming streams with bark and mud. It is known as an industrious worker.
name: Bibarel

flavor: It shakes its head back to front, causing its antennae to hit each other and sound like a xylophone.
name: Kricketot

flavor: It crosses its knifelike arms in front of its chest when it cries. It can compose melodies ad lib.
name: Kricketune

flavor: All of its fur dazzles if danger is sensed. It flees while the foe is momentarily blinded.
name: Shinx

flavor: Its claws loose electricity with enough amperage to cause fainting. They live in small groups.
name: Luxio

flavor: It has eyes that can see through anything. It spots and captures prey hiding behind objects.
name: Luxray

flavor: Over the winter, it closes its bud and endures the cold. In spring, the bud opens and releases pollen.
name: Budew

flavor: It attracts prey with a sweet aroma, then downs it with thorny whips hidden in its arms.
name: Roserade

flavor: It lived in jungles around 100 million years ago. Its skull is as hard as iron.
name: Cranidos

flavor: Its powerful head butt has enough power to shatter even the most durable things upon impact.
name: Rampardos

flavor: A Pokémon that lived in jungles around 100 million years ago. Its facial hide is extremely hard.
name: Shieldon

flavor: Any frontal attack is repulsed. It is a docile Pokémon that feeds on grass and berries.
name: Bastiodon

flavor: To shelter itself from cold, wintry winds, it covers itself with a cloak made of twigs and leaves.
name: Burmy

flavor: When BURMY evolved, its cloak became a part of this Pokémon’s body. The cloak is never shed.
name: Wormadam

flavor: It loves the honey of flowers and steals honey collected by COMBEE.
name: Mothim

flavor: A Pokémon formed by three others. It busily carries sweet floral honey to VESPIQUEN.
name: Combee

flavor: Its abdomen is a honeycomb for grubs. It raises its grubs on honey collected by COMBEE.
name: Vespiquen

flavor: It makes fur balls that crackle with static electricity. It stores them with berries in tree holes.
name: Pachirisu

flavor: It has a flotation sac that is like an inflatable collar. It floats on water with its head out.
name: Buizel

flavor: It floats using its well-developed flotation sac. It assists in the rescues of drowning people.
name: Floatzel

flavor: The small ball holds the nutrients needed for evolution. Apparently, it is very sweet and tasty.
name: Cherubi

flavor: It blooms during times of strong sunlight. It tries to make up for everything it endured as a bud.
name: Cherrim

flavor: Its shape and coloration vary, depending on its habitat.
name: Shellos

flavor: It has a pliable body without any bones. If any part of its body is torn off, it grows right back.
name: Gastrodon

flavor: To eat, it deftly shucks nuts with its two tails. It rarely uses its arms now.
name: Ambipom

flavor: A Pokémon formed by the spirits of people and Pokémon. It loves damp, humid seasons.
name: Drifloon

flavor: It’s drowzy in daytime, but flies off in the evening in big groups. No one knows where they go.
name: Drifblim

flavor: It slams foes by sharply uncoiling its rolled ears. It stings enough to make a grown-up cry in pain.
name: Buneary

flavor: An extremely cautious Pokémon. It cloaks its body with its fluffy ear fur when it senses danger.
name: Lopunny

flavor: Its cries sound like incantations. Those hearing it are tormented by headaches and hallucinations.
name: Mismagius

flavor: Becoming active at night, it is known to swarm with numerous MURKROW in tow.
name: Honchkrow

flavor: It claws if displeased and purrs when affectionate. Its fickleness is very popular among some.
name: Glameow

flavor: It is a brazen brute that barges its way into another Pokémon’s nest and claims it as its own.
name: Purugly

flavor: It emits cries by agitating an orb at the back of its throat. It moves with flouncing hops.
name: Chingling

flavor: It protects itself by spraying a noxious fluid from its rear. The stench lingers for 24 hours.
name: Stunky

flavor: It sprays a vile-smelling fluid from the tip of its tail to attack. Its range is over 160 feet.
name: Skuntank

flavor: Implements shaped like it were discovered in ancient tombs. It is unknown if they are related.
name: Bronzor

flavor: One caused a news sensation when it was dug up at a construction site after a 2,000-year sleep.
name: Bronzong

flavor: It prefers an arid atmosphere. It leaks water that looks like tears when adjusting its moisture level.
name: Bonsly

flavor: It habitually mimics foes. Once mimicked, the foe cannot take its eyes off this Pokémon.
name: Mime-jr

flavor: It loves round white things. It carries an egg-shaped rock in imitation of CHANSEY.
name: Happiny

flavor: It can learn and speak human words. If they gather, they all learn the same saying.
name: Chatot

flavor: A Pokémon that was formed by 108 spirits. It is bound to a fissure in an odd keystone.
name: Spiritomb

flavor: It nests in small, horizontal holes in cave walls. It pounces to catch prey that stray too close.
name: Gible

flavor: There is a long-held belief that medicine made from its scales will heal even incurable illnesses.
name: Gabite

flavor: When it folds up its body and extends its wings, it looks like a jet plane. It flies at sonic speed.
name: Garchomp

flavor: It wolfs down its weight in food once a day, swallowing food whole with almost no chewing.
name: Munchlax

flavor: The aura that emanates from its body intensifies to alert others if it is afraid or sad.
name: Riolu

flavor: It has the ability to sense the auras of all things. It understands human speech.
name: Lucario

flavor: It lives in arid places. Instead of perspiration, it expels grainy sand from its body.
name: Hippopotas

flavor: It blasts internally stored sand from ports on its body to create a towering twister for attack.
name: Hippowdon

flavor: It grips prey with its tail claws and injects poison. It tenaciously hangs on until the poison takes.
name: Skorupi

flavor: It has the power in its clawed arms to make scrap of a car. The tips of its claws release poison.
name: Drapion

flavor: Its cheeks hold poison sacs. It tries to catch foes off guard to jab them with toxic fingers.
name: Croagunk

flavor: Its knuckle claws secrete a toxin so vile that even a scratch could prove fatal.
name: Toxicroak

flavor: It attracts prey with its sweet- smelling saliva, then chomps down. It takes a whole day to eat prey.
name: Carnivine

flavor: After long exposure to sunlight, the patterns on its tail fins shine vividly when darkness arrives.
name: Finneon

flavor: It lives on the deep-sea floor. It attracts prey by flashing the patterns on its four tail fins.
name: Lumineon

flavor: A friendly Pokémon that captures the subtle flows of seawater using its two antennae.
name: Mantyke

flavor: It lives on snowy mountains. Having had little contact with humans, it is boldly inquisitive.
name: Snover

flavor: It whips up blizzards in mountains that are always buried in snow. It is the abominable snowman.
name: Abomasnow

flavor: They live in cold regions, forming groups of four or five that hunt prey with impressive coordination.
name: Weavile

flavor: It evolved from exposure to a special magnetic field. Three units generate magnetism.
name: Magnezone

flavor: It wraps things with its extensible tongue. Getting too close to it will leave you soaked with drool.
name: Lickilicky

flavor: It puts rocks in holes in its palms and uses its muscles to shoot them. GEODUDE are shot at rare times.
name: Rhyperior

flavor: It ensnares prey by extending arms made of vines. Losing arms to predators does not trouble it.
name: Tangrowth

flavor: It pushes the tips of its two tails against the foe, then lets loose with over 20,000 volts of power.
name: Electivire

flavor: It blasts fireballs of over 3,600 degrees F from the ends of its arms. It lives in volcanic craters.
name: Magmortar

flavor: It will never appear where there is strife. Its sightings have become rare recently.
name: Togekiss

flavor: By churning its wings, it creates shock waves that inflict critical internal injuries to foes.
name: Yanmega

flavor: Just like a plant, it uses photosynthesis. As a result, it is always enveloped in clear air.
name: Leafeon

flavor: As a protective technique, it can completely freeze its fur to make its hairs stand like needles.
name: Glaceon

flavor: It observes prey while hanging inverted from branches. When the chance presents itself, it swoops!
name: Gliscor

flavor: Its impressive tusks are made of ice. The population thinned when it turned warm after the ice age.
name: Mamoswine

flavor: Additional software was installed to make it a better Pokémon. It began acting oddly, however.
name: Porygon-z

flavor: A master of courtesy and swordsmanship, it fights using extending swords on its elbows.
name: Gallade
